  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for instantiating a font variant from an <see cref="T:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface" />.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` bundles together the parameters needed to create a specific variation of a typeface — such as which font collection entry to use, which color palette to apply, palette overrides, and variation axis coordinates.

Pass an `SKFontArguments` instance to <see cref="M:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)" /> to produce a new typeface with the specified settings applied.

## Examples

```csharp
// Select the second entry in a font collection and enable a color palette
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 1,
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("color-font.ttf");
using var variant = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
